WEBVTT

01:50.009 --> 01:53.950
[Love Between Lines]

01:54.289 --> 01:56.950
[Episode 5]

02:04.200 --> 02:04.950
I...

02:06.200 --> 02:07.330
Dad, Mom, actually,

02:07.400 --> 02:09.190
I forgot my keys today.

02:09.919 --> 02:11.400
Why didn't you say so earlier?

02:11.400 --> 02:12.750
I brought the spare key.

02:15.560 --> 02:16.150
You did?

02:16.310 --> 02:17.150
L-Let me.

02:17.150 --> 02:17.680
Let me.

02:18.400 --> 02:20.260
Which key is it? There are so many.

02:20.590 --> 02:23.390
You don't even recognize
the key to your own house?

02:23.840 --> 02:24.870
This short one.

02:28.510 --> 02:29.230
Dad! Mom!

02:29.250 --> 02:30.450
I'm opening the door!

02:31.050 --> 02:31.800
What's this about?

02:31.800 --> 02:33.530
We haven't gone deaf, alright?

02:34.040 --> 02:35.040
I-I'm opening it!

02:41.430 --> 02:41.750
Well...

02:41.750 --> 02:42.400
What are you doing?

02:42.400 --> 02:43.360
I dropped the key.

02:43.360 --> 02:44.120
I'll get you slippers.

02:44.120 --> 02:45.920
Why's it so hard to open the door?

02:48.030 --> 02:49.160
Dad, your slippers.

02:52.470 --> 02:53.240
Xiu.

02:53.690 --> 02:55.820
Isn't this coat a bit too large for you?

02:57.160 --> 02:59.120
Oversize is in right now.

02:59.230 --> 03:00.820
I know what oversize is,

03:01.680 --> 03:03.160
but this is a bit too oversized, isn't it?

03:03.160 --> 03:05.160
Well, I'll go return it tomorrow.

03:06.080 --> 03:08.080
You bought another coffee machine?

03:08.760 --> 03:09.690
Coffee machine?

03:10.960 --> 03:12.280
This coffee machine

03:12.710 --> 03:13.870
was a gift from Zhao.

03:13.890 --> 03:16.150
It's an old one she retired from her shop.

03:17.190 --> 03:18.190
This... This

03:18.210 --> 03:20.030
must be quite expensive, isn't it?

03:20.030 --> 03:21.160
It's not expensive.

03:21.430 --> 03:22.490
Just entry-level.

03:22.710 --> 03:23.940
It's really nice.

03:28.040 --> 03:29.470
Mom, why are you going to the balcony?

03:29.470 --> 03:30.400
I want to open the window.
It's too stuffy in here.

03:30.400 --> 03:31.190
Let me. Let me.

03:31.190 --> 03:32.870
Let me do it.

03:40.520 --> 03:41.000
Here.

03:41.400 --> 03:41.840
This.

03:42.520 --> 03:43.920
I've got it ready for you.

03:45.870 --> 03:47.030
Dad, Mom, how about

03:47.130 --> 03:48.500
we go out to eat instead?

03:49.750 --> 03:50.880
It'll be ready soon.

03:51.030 --> 03:52.360
Yeah, everything's ready-made.

03:52.360 --> 03:53.560
Why go out?

03:57.520 --> 03:58.470
My phone's dead.

04:06.740 --> 04:08.140
Can this bowl hold it all?

04:08.480 --> 04:10.080
This one seems even smaller.

04:15.630 --> 04:16.390
Xiu.

04:16.630 --> 04:18.120
Do you have a bigger soup bowl?

04:18.120 --> 04:19.600
Yes. I'll get it for you.

04:22.270 --> 04:23.000
Felix.

04:23.120 --> 04:24.040
You've looked over the new

04:24.040 --> 04:26.440
instance dungeon design proposal, right?

04:27.050 --> 04:27.490
Yes.

04:27.720 --> 04:28.720
It's been handed over to the 3D team

04:28.720 --> 04:30.320
for modeling and rendering.

04:31.430 --> 04:33.000
Alright, let's touch base again
when needed.

04:33.000 --> 04:34.080
Okay, bye-bye.

04:37.120 --> 04:39.850
You really are acting like
a hands-off boss, aren't you?

04:39.850 --> 04:41.170
I told you

04:41.440 --> 04:43.770
I'm only responsible for the design part.

04:45.420 --> 04:47.360
[Missed call from Hu Xiu]

04:48.800 --> 04:49.390
Wait.

04:49.510 --> 04:50.750
Haven't you talked things out

04:50.750 --> 04:52.120
with Hu Xiu?

04:52.120 --> 04:53.600
Why is she still calling me?

04:53.600 --> 04:54.430
Maybe

04:54.700 --> 04:56.110
you two are just close.

04:56.630 --> 04:57.600
Bro, even so, that's no reason

04:57.600 --> 04:59.330
to call me a dozen times, right?

05:08.600 --> 05:09.360
Hello,

05:09.480 --> 05:12.660
the subscriber you dialed
cannot be connected for the moment.

05:12.660 --> 05:14.420
Please try again later.

05:17.050 --> 05:17.930
I'll head back.

05:19.800 --> 05:20.400
By the way,

05:21.300 --> 05:22.890
give Hu Xiu my contact info.

05:23.160 --> 05:25.820
That way, she won't keep
bothering you anymore.

05:44.480 --> 05:45.159
Have a try.

05:46.600 --> 05:47.159
Not bad.

05:47.850 --> 05:48.830
Add some more salt.

05:48.830 --> 05:49.520
More salt?

06:04.500 --> 06:07.360
[Please do not enter]

06:14.630 --> 06:15.430
Xiu?

06:16.260 --> 06:17.060
What's wrong?

06:17.360 --> 06:20.090
Can you go buy a bottle of cooking wine
at the lane entrance?

06:20.090 --> 06:23.290
Cooking wine is one of those things
you can skip, isn't it?

06:23.410 --> 06:24.970
H-How about I go?

06:25.640 --> 06:27.120
Dad, I was just kidding.

06:27.140 --> 06:28.490
Don't bother. I'll go.

06:29.380 --> 06:30.060
My phone.

06:33.480 --> 06:35.810
Ms. Hu, this is the tenant's phone number.

06:55.390 --> 06:55.950
Move, move.

06:55.950 --> 06:57.070
What are you doing?

06:57.470 --> 06:58.030
What's happening?

06:58.030 --> 06:59.590
Here's the thing:

06:59.920 --> 07:01.000
my parents are here to visit me.

07:01.000 --> 07:02.530
They're in there right now.

07:03.030 --> 07:05.860
I didn't tell them
I'd rented the place out.

07:06.750 --> 07:08.950
So could you find somewhere nearby

07:08.950 --> 07:09.360
to wait for a bit?

07:09.360 --> 07:10.120
I promise

07:10.270 --> 07:11.330
it won't take long.

07:12.000 --> 07:12.680
Mom.

07:17.310 --> 07:18.270
This is...

07:20.670 --> 07:21.670
My colleague.

07:23.860 --> 07:25.260
How should I address you?

07:27.480 --> 07:28.430
Uncle, Auntie.

07:29.340 --> 07:30.420
Just call me Yu.

07:49.590 --> 07:51.120
Mom, actually,

07:51.310 --> 07:52.950
Yu's already eaten.

07:53.270 --> 07:54.000
Right?

07:55.390 --> 07:56.000
Yeah.

07:56.290 --> 07:57.890
Auntie, I've already eaten.

07:58.940 --> 08:00.140
But I'm hungry again.

08:01.830 --> 08:03.560
Then hurry up and start eating.

08:05.020 --> 08:06.070
Yu, right?

08:06.090 --> 08:06.450
Yes.

08:06.480 --> 08:06.950
Here,

08:07.070 --> 08:07.870
try this.

08:08.600 --> 08:10.060
See if it suits your taste.

08:10.190 --> 08:11.250
Thank you, Auntie.

08:11.920 --> 08:12.650
Come on, eat.

08:19.750 --> 08:20.560
Xiu.

08:21.920 --> 08:22.720
Why

08:23.190 --> 08:24.920
haven't I heard you

08:25.240 --> 08:27.040
mention this colleague before?

08:28.480 --> 08:30.630
Well, we've just become colleagues.
We're not very close.

08:30.630 --> 08:31.830
If you're not close,

08:32.169 --> 08:33.900
why would he come to your place?

08:35.130 --> 08:37.720
He's here for a very important document.

08:37.750 --> 08:38.830
What document?

08:46.920 --> 08:48.050
A leasing contract.

08:51.330 --> 08:53.160
I left my leasing contract with Hu Xiu.

08:53.160 --> 08:55.440
Our company mentioned a housing allowance,

08:55.440 --> 08:56.990
so I asked Hu Xiu to help me apply for it.

08:56.990 --> 08:58.850
So you live in a rented place, huh?

09:00.910 --> 09:02.390
I was just curious.

09:02.470 --> 09:03.510
Go ahead, go ahead.

09:03.510 --> 09:03.910
I just got something stuck in throat.

09:03.910 --> 09:05.170
Renting is quite nice.

09:05.580 --> 09:06.100
Yes,

09:06.270 --> 09:08.110
I also think renting is pretty good.

09:08.110 --> 09:09.440
If I could have a nice landlord,

09:09.440 --> 09:10.900
that would be even better.

09:15.720 --> 09:16.910
Dad, Mom, I'm full.

09:16.910 --> 09:17.870
We're both done eating.

09:17.870 --> 09:18.480
Come on.

09:19.510 --> 09:20.390
I'll see him off,

09:20.390 --> 09:22.080
just in case he doesn't know the way.

09:22.080 --> 09:23.390
But we've only just started eating.

09:23.390 --> 09:23.840
You haven't finished yet.

09:23.840 --> 09:25.120
We're done. We're full.

09:25.120 --> 09:26.150
At least finish your meal before leaving.

09:26.150 --> 09:27.120
We ate plenty.

09:29.600 --> 09:30.150
Let's go.

09:32.210 --> 09:33.730
Why such a rush?

09:55.630 --> 09:56.320
Go on, tell me—

09:56.320 --> 09:58.050
how do you plan to resolve this?

09:59.150 --> 10:00.610
They'll definitely leave

10:00.750 --> 10:01.610
within 2 hours.

10:02.150 --> 10:03.030
If you don't want to wait,

10:03.030 --> 10:04.430
I can put you up in a hotel.

10:05.960 --> 10:06.960
Forget the hotel.

10:07.010 --> 10:09.210
But we must sign a new leasing contract.

10:13.910 --> 10:14.750
Hello, Ms. Hu.

10:14.750 --> 10:15.550
This is

10:15.550 --> 10:16.230
Dynamism

10:16.230 --> 10:17.550
Design Studio.

10:18.240 --> 10:19.390
Dynamism?

10:20.000 --> 10:20.480
Yes.

10:20.670 --> 10:22.240
I'd like to know if you have time tomorrow

10:22.240 --> 10:24.320
to come to our studio for an interview.

10:24.320 --> 10:25.200
I-Is it really

10:25.200 --> 10:26.150
Dynamism?

10:26.150 --> 10:26.840
Yes.

10:26.990 --> 10:30.190
I tried to call you this afternoon,
but you didn't answer.

10:31.000 --> 10:32.510
Wait, I-I'm sorry.

10:31.160 --> 10:35.460
♪ Under the streetlight,
I grow increasingly weary ♪

10:32.510 --> 10:33.550
I missed it.

10:33.670 --> 10:34.070
You...

10:34.840 --> 10:35.440
H-Hold on.

10:35.440 --> 10:36.840
So you

10:36.840 --> 10:38.720
received my resume, right?

10:37.250 --> 10:42.090
♪ A few specks of dust
drift by in the wind ♪

10:39.240 --> 10:41.300
What position am I interviewing for?

10:41.360 --> 10:42.960
We've reviewed your information.

10:42.960 --> 10:45.000
You're interviewing for a position
in the design department.

10:44.370 --> 10:48.530
♪ The girl who once
basked in the sunlight ♪

10:45.000 --> 10:47.200
The interview is scheduled for
2 p.m. tomorrow.

10:47.200 --> 10:49.210
I'll send the address to your email
shortly.

10:49.210 --> 10:52.130
♪ Where did she go to play? ♪

10:50.150 --> 10:52.570
Okay, no problem.
I'll definitely be there.

10:52.570 --> 10:55.550
♪ I don't understand either ♪

10:52.630 --> 10:53.360
Thank you.

10:53.670 --> 10:54.360
Thank you.

10:57.780 --> 11:01.610
♪ Flicking through old chat logs ♪

11:03.860 --> 11:08.740
♪ I just realized the replies
were somewhat delayed ♪

11:06.280 --> 11:09.090
It's just an interview notification,
not a job offer.

11:09.090 --> 11:10.300
Is it really worth getting this excited?

11:09.880 --> 11:15.870
♪ At the crossroads of choices,
amidst the bustling crowd ♪

11:11.490 --> 11:12.750
You don't understand.

11:14.150 --> 11:15.600
Even though I've been telling my parents

11:15.600 --> 11:17.080
all kinds of nonsense,

11:17.110 --> 11:24.380
♪ Who hasn't paid the price
and still fallen short? ♪

11:18.120 --> 11:20.580
deep down, I've actually been
a bit nervous.

11:22.150 --> 11:24.350
I was worried I'd chosen the wrong path.

11:24.400 --> 11:28.950
♪ Stand with me tonight,
look at the starlight ♪

11:24.600 --> 11:25.600
Because

11:25.600 --> 11:28.000
this isn't just an interview opportunity—

11:29.000 --> 11:30.910
it's recognition from

11:29.760 --> 11:35.810
♪ Even if the plot is changed dramatically
by fate again ♪

11:30.910 --> 11:32.200
my favorite studio.

11:32.960 --> 11:34.360
It's worth celebrating.

11:34.900 --> 11:35.690
Ms. Cai,

11:35.750 --> 11:36.840
a piece of
"good -luck" persimmon cake please.

11:36.490 --> 11:42.710
♪ I know the dark clouds will still come ♪

11:38.630 --> 11:39.580
Make it two.

11:40.550 --> 11:42.480
Having dessert this late at night?

11:43.410 --> 11:49.350
♪ But in this world,
there will always be someone ♪

11:52.460 --> 11:55.860
♪ Who looks forward
with the same hope as me ♪

12:00.120 --> 12:01.080
The winners of the new
Global Architecture & Design Awards

12:01.080 --> 12:03.260
for Architectural Design Consultants
have been announced.

12:03.260 --> 12:05.670
D Design Studio has once again
made the list.

12:05.670 --> 12:06.660
At the award ceremony,

12:06.660 --> 12:08.960
the designer still did not
make a public appearance.

12:08.960 --> 12:10.080
We boldly speculate

12:10.080 --> 12:11.480
that this refusal of public exposure

12:11.480 --> 12:13.030
reflects the designer's philosophy

12:13.030 --> 12:15.090
of letting the work speak for itself.

12:43.270 --> 12:45.150
Hello, I'm here for an interview.

12:45.560 --> 12:47.020
What's your name, please?

12:47.120 --> 12:47.840
Hu Xiu.

12:48.600 --> 12:49.730
Please come with me.

12:55.430 --> 12:57.080
I've told you this design won't work.

12:57.080 --> 12:58.320
That's because of your lack of ability.

12:58.320 --> 12:59.200
How many times have I
given you instructions?

12:59.200 --> 13:00.270
What kind of mess is this revision?

13:00.270 --> 13:01.080
I've already revised it 3 times.

13:01.080 --> 13:02.390
What's wrong with my ability?

13:02.390 --> 13:03.030
I won't waste words on you. Come on.

13:03.030 --> 13:04.690
I'll draw it out for you. Look.

13:06.690 --> 13:07.890
It's alright, Ms. Hu.

13:08.200 --> 13:09.550
When they're working on creative projects,

13:09.550 --> 13:10.630
they tend to be quite temperamental.

13:10.630 --> 13:12.090
They'll make up in no time.

13:15.960 --> 13:17.630
Please wait here for a moment.

13:17.630 --> 13:19.480
Someone will come out
to guide you inside shortly.

13:19.480 --> 13:20.270
Good luck.

13:20.490 --> 13:21.180
Thank you.

13:38.600 --> 13:41.150
Mr. Xiao never used to
attend initial interviews.

13:41.150 --> 13:42.970
Why is he making an exception today?

13:42.970 --> 13:43.910
I'm not sure either.

13:43.910 --> 13:45.440
Mr. Xiao only notified me last night

13:45.440 --> 13:47.770
that he would attend the interview today.

14:06.190 --> 14:07.190
Everyone's here.

14:08.400 --> 14:09.280
Let's begin.

14:11.670 --> 14:12.930
Hu Xiu, please come in.

14:48.710 --> 14:54.570
♪ Life lays out the outline of my scenes ♪

14:55.810 --> 14:59.280
♪ The last act
was a monologue in a dream ♪

15:00.480 --> 15:04.250
♪ And in the next,
I wander through the city's noise ♪

15:03.260 --> 15:04.530
Why is it him?

15:05.410 --> 15:08.480
♪ So many arrivals
that turned out to be nothing ♪

15:08.600 --> 15:09.530
Please sit down.

15:10.060 --> 15:13.710
♪ I'm counting the beats of the clock ♪

15:14.770 --> 15:18.570
♪ I can't tell which platform
is for leaving or returning ♪

15:19.440 --> 15:23.710
♪ Until you walk toward me ♪

15:19.750 --> 15:21.120
Hello, Ms. Hu.

15:21.510 --> 15:23.110
I'm Dong Qi, the HR Director.

15:23.150 --> 15:25.390
These two are partners at our studio.

15:25.140 --> 15:28.720
♪ And my breath softens ♪

15:25.720 --> 15:27.180
That's Ms. Zhou, Zhou Yan.

15:27.320 --> 15:28.030
And this is the founder of

15:28.030 --> 15:28.750
Dynamism,

15:28.750 --> 15:30.080
Mr. Xiao, Xiao Zhiyu.

15:30.240 --> 15:34.620
♪ I forget every absurd line ♪

15:33.510 --> 15:34.700
Founder?

15:35.390 --> 15:39.370
♪ Because of you ♪

15:39.720 --> 15:40.440
Ms. Hu?

15:40.320 --> 15:47.150
♪ All those postures, it turns out
you were not part of my story ♪

15:43.230 --> 15:44.230
Hello, everyone.

15:44.910 --> 15:47.080
Please introduce yourself first.

15:48.550 --> 15:49.480
My name is Hu Xiu.

15:49.750 --> 15:51.720
I majored in architecture
as an undergraduate.

15:51.720 --> 15:52.600
After graduating,

15:52.600 --> 15:55.150
I worked as a GM assistant
at Shiyuan Real Estate.

15:55.150 --> 15:56.720
I resigned recently

15:56.910 --> 16:00.110
am now looking for a job
related to architectural design.

16:02.030 --> 16:02.550
Ms. Hu,

16:02.550 --> 16:04.320
I see that in your previous job,

16:04.320 --> 16:06.430
you became a GM assistant
in less than 3 years,

16:06.430 --> 16:08.020
which shows you were highly valued.

16:08.020 --> 16:09.950
Your salary and benefits
must have been quite generous.

16:09.950 --> 16:11.920
So why did you choose to resign?

16:14.940 --> 16:16.870
I chose Shiyuan Real Estate before

16:17.200 --> 16:19.230
due to certain practical factors.

16:19.870 --> 16:20.870
But now,

16:21.150 --> 16:22.360
I want to make a change

16:22.740 --> 16:24.500
and do what I truly enjoy.

16:25.920 --> 16:26.830
But

16:26.860 --> 16:29.720
architecture is
a highly specialized profession.

16:30.030 --> 16:31.550
How do you plan to make up for
the three-year gap

16:31.550 --> 16:33.840
and lag in your professional skills,

16:34.150 --> 16:35.600
and how can you prove

16:35.600 --> 16:37.750
that you're qualified for this position?

16:37.750 --> 16:39.030
I haven't had any project practice

16:39.030 --> 16:41.270
over the past 3 years,

16:42.860 --> 16:44.720
but I've never stopped learning.

16:45.000 --> 16:46.000
If that's the case,

16:46.000 --> 16:46.960
do you mind

16:46.960 --> 16:48.420
answering a few questions

16:48.750 --> 16:50.270
related to your profession?

16:50.270 --> 16:50.910
Not at all.

16:51.630 --> 16:54.600
Regarding the criteria for
selecting building structures,

16:54.600 --> 16:56.510
under what circumstances do you think

16:56.510 --> 16:58.790
frame structures would be preferred?

16:59.910 --> 17:01.870
For commercial buildings that require

17:01.870 --> 17:03.200
a relatively high level of
spatial flexibility—

17:03.200 --> 17:05.690
such as shopping malls, office buildings,

17:05.720 --> 17:07.079
and art centers—

17:07.099 --> 17:10.030
frame structures are usually
the preferred choice.

17:10.069 --> 17:11.880
This is because within frame structures,

17:11.880 --> 17:14.440
non-load-bearing infill walls
or partitions

17:14.440 --> 17:17.040
can be relatively easily
modified or removed.

17:19.640 --> 17:20.680
In your opinion,

17:20.790 --> 17:23.109
what's the role of sustainability

17:23.109 --> 17:25.020
in architectural design?

17:30.920 --> 17:31.720
Actually,

17:31.720 --> 17:35.030
sustainable development
is a core principle

17:35.030 --> 17:37.640
of contemporary architectural design.

17:38.070 --> 17:42.000
By integrating those eco-technologies
and green innovations,

17:42.100 --> 17:44.490
like photovoltaic generation systems

17:44.520 --> 17:48.670
or water recycling systems
in our commercial projects.

17:49.170 --> 17:51.960
We not only mitigate
the environmental impact,

17:51.980 --> 17:56.980
but also significantly save
the general cost for our customers.

17:59.520 --> 18:00.440
Well answered.

18:02.710 --> 18:03.770
Tell me about this.

18:12.790 --> 18:14.200
This is a project I worked on

18:14.200 --> 18:16.410
for the UIA-HYP Cup Competition
during college.

18:16.410 --> 18:17.850
It's a beautiful design.

18:18.660 --> 18:19.810
It's quite nice indeed.

18:19.810 --> 18:22.310
Following the design style of
traditional Jiangnan courtyards,

18:22.310 --> 18:23.720
reading in the corridors

18:23.900 --> 18:25.920
not only creates a unique atmosphere,

18:25.920 --> 18:28.180
but also brings people closer together.

18:32.150 --> 18:33.680
However, in architecture,

18:33.720 --> 18:36.200
beauty and ambience alone aren't enough.

18:38.680 --> 18:39.550
Do you know there's a fatal flaw

18:39.550 --> 18:40.830
in your design?

18:49.140 --> 18:49.820
I do.

18:59.680 --> 19:01.160
In a frame structure,

19:01.440 --> 19:02.340
beams and columns

19:02.340 --> 19:04.730
are the most important
load-bearing components.

19:04.730 --> 19:06.450
In pursuit of a sense of openness,

19:06.450 --> 19:08.650
I failed to reserve sufficient
load-bearing components

19:08.650 --> 19:10.340
to carry the additional loads.

19:10.340 --> 19:12.490
As a result, once any one of them fails,

19:12.520 --> 19:14.040
the axial compression ratio
of the structural system

19:14.040 --> 19:15.370
would exceed the limit,

19:16.920 --> 19:20.250
leading to a progressive collapse
of the entire structure.

19:20.560 --> 19:21.640
I used to believe

19:22.030 --> 19:23.790
that the most important thing
in architecture

19:23.790 --> 19:24.880
was personality

19:25.070 --> 19:25.960
and style.

19:26.350 --> 19:27.620
As long as they were strong enough,

19:27.620 --> 19:30.080
they'd be able to
catch people's attention.

19:30.920 --> 19:32.520
Now I see that's not the case.

19:33.140 --> 19:34.140
In this industry,

19:34.880 --> 19:36.900
the most important thing is
and will always be

19:36.900 --> 19:37.770
safety.

19:40.720 --> 19:42.270
According to preliminary investigation,

19:42.270 --> 19:43.440
the collapse of
the Xincheng Sports Stadium

19:43.440 --> 19:45.350
was caused by non-compliant
project drawing reviews.

19:45.350 --> 19:47.880
The contractor unauthorizedly
used substandard steel,

19:47.880 --> 19:49.010
resulting in a partial collapse.

19:49.010 --> 19:50.820
Besides the load-bearing
beams and columns,

19:50.820 --> 19:53.510
I would also replace the materials
of the building's exterior facade

19:53.510 --> 19:54.550
to add texture,

19:54.550 --> 19:56.830
so that when sunlight filters in,

19:56.830 --> 19:58.490
the spatial layers will be more nuanced.

19:58.490 --> 19:59.480
For areas like the reading zone,

19:59.480 --> 20:01.420
I'd make the space
more open and transparent,

20:01.420 --> 20:03.310
so readers can enjoy better lighting

20:03.310 --> 20:04.980
while reading.

20:05.670 --> 20:07.070
The core of architecture

20:07.370 --> 20:08.480
is always people.

20:15.350 --> 20:16.550
Very well, Ms. Hu.

20:17.000 --> 20:18.470
That concludes today's interview.

20:18.470 --> 20:20.890
We'll inform you of the interview result
within 3 days.

20:20.890 --> 20:22.310
Please remember to check your email.

20:22.310 --> 20:22.960
Thank you.

20:23.360 --> 20:24.030
Thanks.

20:45.480 --> 20:46.370
What's this?

20:46.390 --> 20:47.590
It's just a painting.

20:48.400 --> 20:49.950
So he's here for inspiration.

20:49.950 --> 20:51.480
It's painted quite nicely.

20:51.720 --> 20:53.890
You can tell it's a bookstore?

20:56.520 --> 20:58.090
So I'm the real clown here.

21:08.310 --> 21:09.000
Mr. Xiao.

21:11.400 --> 21:12.730
What are you looking at?

21:13.270 --> 21:14.030
Nothing.

21:17.640 --> 21:19.640
The next interview is in 20 minutes.

21:20.000 --> 21:20.680
Got it.

21:23.400 --> 21:24.260
Anything else?

21:25.420 --> 21:27.490
I received your email.

21:27.920 --> 21:29.400
You've signed up for

21:29.400 --> 21:31.530
the Lyman Hotel project competition?

21:31.830 --> 21:32.400
Yes.

21:33.640 --> 21:36.100
So this is
what you've been busy with lately.

21:37.650 --> 21:39.510
I know what you're worried about.

21:45.340 --> 21:47.650
I've always supported your decisions,

21:48.110 --> 21:49.000
but

21:49.000 --> 21:50.590
Lyman has always worked with

21:50.590 --> 21:52.630
publicly listed companies like Zhuling.

21:52.630 --> 21:54.680
Our studio has only been established
for less than 5 years.

21:54.680 --> 21:56.810
You think my design isn't good enough?

21:57.510 --> 21:59.830
Using lane elements to create

21:59.830 --> 22:02.830
a landmark hotel that is both retro
and rich in multicultural character—

22:02.830 --> 22:04.920
the design and concept are both excellent.

22:04.920 --> 22:06.350
I have no doubt about that.

22:06.350 --> 22:07.680
Lyman has abundant funding

22:07.680 --> 22:09.620
and offers great creative freedom.

22:09.620 --> 22:12.230
The project allows architects
to fully express themselves.

22:12.230 --> 22:13.360
That's exactly why

22:13.640 --> 22:14.640
every one of their projects

22:14.640 --> 22:16.240
wins international awards.

22:17.470 --> 22:19.600
Securing an award of that caliber

22:20.000 --> 22:20.960
would be a major boost

22:20.960 --> 22:22.110
for Dynamism.

22:23.070 --> 22:24.530
That's an odd thing to say.

22:25.000 --> 22:28.600
You're not entering the competition
just to win awards, are you?

22:28.800 --> 22:29.840
Why not?

22:30.160 --> 22:33.360
I do architecture to win awards
and make a name for myself.

22:48.230 --> 22:49.880
I have a question:

22:49.960 --> 22:50.310
has

22:50.310 --> 22:50.920
Dynamism

22:50.920 --> 22:52.580
Architectural Design Studio

22:52.710 --> 22:54.270
ever changed its founder?

22:54.480 --> 22:56.830
Usually they don't change founders.

22:57.100 --> 22:58.690
Any gossip?

22:59.110 --> 23:01.600
No, just letting my imagination run a bit.

23:03.010 --> 23:05.140
What kind of question was that?

23:08.590 --> 23:09.350
Zhao,

23:10.130 --> 23:11.610
I have a question for you.

23:12.240 --> 23:14.030
Do you think those successful people

23:14.030 --> 23:15.160
have any little quirks

23:15.160 --> 23:16.420
in their private lives

23:16.590 --> 23:19.070
that no one knows about?

23:21.670 --> 23:22.990
Quirks?

23:23.960 --> 23:24.760
What's wrong?

23:26.240 --> 23:28.510
You've come to the right person.

23:29.200 --> 23:29.800
Come here.

23:36.200 --> 23:38.440
I'm asking about legal quirks.

23:39.310 --> 23:41.000
Legal ones?

23:41.440 --> 23:43.000
There are plenty of those too.

23:43.000 --> 23:44.890
I heard that chain gym's founder

23:45.110 --> 23:45.830
has a quirk—

23:45.830 --> 23:47.230
he likes washing dishes.

23:47.550 --> 23:50.350
The dirtier and more disgusting
the dishes are,

23:50.350 --> 23:52.130
the more satisfaction
he gets from cleaning them.

23:52.130 --> 23:53.530
The dirtier, the better.

23:59.000 --> 24:00.570
Anything else?

24:02.590 --> 24:06.190
There's an internet-famous restaurant
on the street behind us,

24:06.200 --> 24:07.640
and their staff told me

24:07.790 --> 24:09.640
their boss likes to collect hats.

24:09.640 --> 24:11.970
What's so special about collecting hats?

24:12.030 --> 24:13.160
The ones he collects

24:13.440 --> 24:14.830
aren't ordinary hats.

24:21.750 --> 24:22.350
Also,

24:22.680 --> 24:24.790
that tea house we often visit,

24:24.990 --> 24:27.180
the owner with all those muscles,
remember?

24:27.180 --> 24:29.160
Do you know what
his favorite exercise is?

24:29.160 --> 24:29.760
Exercise?

24:30.200 --> 24:31.130
Weightlifting?

24:33.070 --> 24:34.400
Dancing.

24:45.580 --> 24:47.240
There's one that's even more shocking.

24:47.240 --> 24:48.770
That guy who's always on TV,

24:48.790 --> 24:50.110
that super masculine big shot,

24:50.110 --> 24:51.060
what's his name again?

24:51.060 --> 24:52.790
He's one of my husband's clients.

24:52.790 --> 24:53.680
-You know, he...
-Alright, alright.

24:53.680 --> 24:55.000
I don't really want to know

24:55.000 --> 24:57.730
the secrets of
those successful people anymore.

24:58.800 --> 25:00.840
You know, those successful people

25:01.260 --> 25:03.720
are in high positions
with lots of pressure,

25:03.720 --> 25:05.590
so having some strange hobbies

25:05.880 --> 25:07.540
is actually understandable.

25:09.600 --> 25:12.460
Why are you suddenly asking me
a question like this?

25:12.640 --> 25:15.770
Did you get to know
some successful person or something?

25:20.200 --> 25:21.000
Who is it?

25:21.350 --> 25:21.640
Hello.

25:21.640 --> 25:23.440
When are we going to sign
the new leasing contract?

25:23.440 --> 25:24.240
Just a moment.

25:31.350 --> 25:32.790
That concludes today's interview.

25:32.790 --> 25:35.350
We'll inform you of the result
within 3 days.

25:35.480 --> 25:36.200
Thank you.

25:36.660 --> 25:37.180
Okay.

25:37.380 --> 25:38.100
Thank you.

25:39.100 --> 25:40.700
Follow me. I'll show you out.

25:48.070 --> 25:49.870
This last candidate was decent.

25:50.270 --> 25:52.730
Good education,
with overseas study experience.

25:52.730 --> 25:55.590
It's just his salary expectations
are way too high.

25:56.110 --> 25:57.270
Judging by his attitude,

25:57.270 --> 25:59.800
it'll be hard to negotiate
within our budget.

26:00.640 --> 26:02.340
Then there's that one named Hu Xiu...

26:02.340 --> 26:04.070
I'll bring the contract over tonight.

26:04.070 --> 26:05.640
My questions were a bit tricky,

26:05.640 --> 26:06.830
but she answered them well.

26:06.830 --> 26:07.590
It's just a pity that

26:07.590 --> 26:09.350
she hasn't accumulated any experience
these years.

26:09.350 --> 26:10.590
Not sure whether she'll be able to adapt

26:10.590 --> 26:12.450
after transferring to this role.

26:13.920 --> 26:15.000
So,

26:15.160 --> 26:15.880
Mr. Xiao,

26:17.030 --> 26:19.560
what's your opinion on
these two candidates?

26:31.440 --> 26:31.960
Mr. Xiao.

26:31.470 --> 26:32.380
[House Leasing Contract]

26:31.960 --> 26:32.640
I've made some minor revisions

26:32.640 --> 26:33.790
to this contract.

26:33.790 --> 26:35.850
Please check if there are any issues.

26:47.240 --> 26:48.090
During the lease term,

26:48.090 --> 26:49.790
the landlord promises to
provide the tenant with

26:49.790 --> 26:51.320
the most pleasant service,

26:51.680 --> 26:53.430
meeting all the tenant's needs,

26:53.430 --> 26:56.030
respecting all of
the tenant's privacy and...

26:58.510 --> 26:59.200
Quirks?

27:02.110 --> 27:06.440
And commit to keeping them confidential
unconditionally and indefinitely,

27:08.160 --> 27:10.220
including after the lease term ends.

27:16.170 --> 27:17.230
I'm fine with that.

27:17.680 --> 27:18.400
However,

27:18.920 --> 27:20.510
I don't want any more

27:20.750 --> 27:22.520
unexpected situations to occur.

27:22.520 --> 27:23.170
I'm sorry.

27:23.550 --> 27:25.810
My parents came unexpectedly last time.

27:26.240 --> 27:27.240
But don't worry.

27:27.350 --> 27:28.160
I'll try my best

27:28.160 --> 27:29.830
to keep them from coming here.

27:30.510 --> 27:31.310
Try your best?

27:32.240 --> 27:35.110
You still haven't told them
that you've rented the place out?

27:35.110 --> 27:37.310
When Chen Dabao caused trouble before,

27:37.330 --> 27:38.730
so many neighbors saw it.

27:38.830 --> 27:40.830
They could tell your parents anytime.

27:40.830 --> 27:41.590
They won't.

27:44.480 --> 27:46.480
My father had an accident years ago

27:46.480 --> 27:47.610
and injured his leg.

27:48.240 --> 27:48.880
Since then,

27:48.880 --> 27:52.480
he hasn't really liked interacting with
the people in this lane.

27:52.590 --> 27:54.720
Maybe he doesn't want them to pity him.

27:58.140 --> 27:59.120
But I have no obligation

27:59.120 --> 28:01.270
to hide things from your parents for you.

28:01.270 --> 28:02.400
You dare not confess to them

28:02.400 --> 28:03.960
because in fact, you don't believe

28:03.960 --> 28:06.290
you can succeed in architectural design.

28:07.950 --> 28:09.370
If you're just temporarily unemployed

28:09.370 --> 28:11.070
and need to rent out the place
as a stopgap,

28:11.070 --> 28:13.270
what's so hard about telling them that?

28:13.840 --> 28:15.950
The night your parents came, you mentioned

28:15.950 --> 28:18.410
you were worried that
you might've chosen the wrong path.

28:18.410 --> 28:20.140
Well, I need to tell you, Ms. Hu,

28:20.400 --> 28:22.930
it's hard for a job candidate
who's still doubting themselves

28:22.930 --> 28:25.190
to convince others to give them a chance.

28:31.260 --> 28:31.830
Mr. Xiao.

28:32.790 --> 28:34.590
I only said those things to you that day

28:34.590 --> 28:36.520
because I considered you a friend.

28:37.380 --> 28:39.640
I didn't expect it to become my weakness

28:39.740 --> 28:41.530
and your reason to reject me.

28:46.510 --> 28:47.790
But I still want to say

28:48.030 --> 28:49.830
that I've never doubted myself.

28:51.160 --> 28:52.450
From the day I quit
without another job lined up,

28:52.450 --> 28:53.450
I've made up my mind

28:53.450 --> 28:55.480
that no matter how difficult
the road ahead is,

28:55.480 --> 28:56.790
I would never give up.

28:57.830 --> 28:58.630
The reason why

28:58.920 --> 29:00.520
I've kept it from them is that

29:01.480 --> 29:03.000
I've been dealing with

29:03.000 --> 29:04.610
a lot of frustrating things lately,

29:04.610 --> 29:06.830
and I don't want them to worry

29:06.830 --> 29:08.160
about me changing jobs.

29:08.270 --> 29:09.270
That's all.

29:12.680 --> 29:13.750
But anyway,

29:14.350 --> 29:15.920
my request

29:16.110 --> 29:17.270
was indeed abrupt.

29:18.270 --> 29:18.960
I'm sorry.

29:19.920 --> 29:20.450
Mr. Xiao.

29:20.640 --> 29:22.200
I won't bother you any further.

29:22.200 --> 29:22.750
Goodbye.

29:44.200 --> 29:46.060
Zhao, want to come out for dinner?

29:58.450 --> 29:59.250
Zhao.

29:59.730 --> 30:01.820
I messed up another interview.

30:07.380 --> 30:08.180
Where are you?

30:14.160 --> 30:14.880
What?

30:15.440 --> 30:17.070
So that difficult tenant
you mentioned last time

30:17.070 --> 30:18.640
is the boss of Dynamism?

30:21.160 --> 30:22.760
They're not the same person.

30:22.820 --> 30:24.020
But in a way, they are.

30:25.750 --> 30:26.680
I was planning

30:26.680 --> 30:28.720
to have a good talk with him today.

30:28.920 --> 30:31.350
He's a designer I've always admired,
you know?

30:31.350 --> 30:32.070
If this were in the past,

30:32.070 --> 30:32.920
I'd have been so happy

30:32.920 --> 30:35.030
and excited to get to know him.

30:35.880 --> 30:37.090
But now, just thinking that

30:37.090 --> 30:38.550
as soon as I got to know him,

30:38.980 --> 30:40.300
he rejected me—

30:40.920 --> 30:44.120
I feel like I'd have been better off
not knowing him at all.

30:45.120 --> 30:45.720
Thank you.

30:49.480 --> 30:50.160
Xiu.

30:50.440 --> 30:51.720
From my point of view,

30:51.720 --> 30:52.720
you two crossing paths at all

30:52.720 --> 30:53.830
is a kind of fate.

30:54.680 --> 30:55.790
He may have rejected you now,

30:55.790 --> 30:58.190
but he might acknowledge you
in the future.

30:58.400 --> 30:59.200
No, no, no.

30:59.410 --> 31:01.070
There's no future between us.

31:01.310 --> 31:03.440
There are many details you don't know.

31:04.280 --> 31:05.270
Now that I think about it,

31:05.270 --> 31:06.590
every word I said

31:06.590 --> 31:07.830
and every move I made

31:08.070 --> 31:09.480
foreshadowed

31:10.350 --> 31:12.280
the outcome of today's interview.

31:29.830 --> 31:30.400
Zhao.

31:31.350 --> 31:33.280
What I'm drinking is juice, right?

31:33.940 --> 31:35.670
Yes, it is juice. What's wrong?

31:36.920 --> 31:39.440
Then why am I hallucinating?

31:58.200 --> 31:59.200
So, Mr. Xiao,

31:59.630 --> 32:02.160
what's your opinion on
these two candidates?

32:03.520 --> 32:05.640
Recruitment is always a two-way choice.

32:05.640 --> 32:07.440
At least I didn't sense

32:07.440 --> 32:08.110
that the person just now

32:08.110 --> 32:10.040
had any expectations of Dynamism.

32:10.590 --> 32:11.720
So,

32:12.140 --> 32:13.220
you mean...

32:14.270 --> 32:15.400
Let's pick Hu Xiu.

32:16.000 --> 32:17.680
Although she has a three-year gap,

32:17.680 --> 32:19.280
her fundamentals are solid.

32:19.600 --> 32:20.350
People like her

32:20.350 --> 32:23.480
are less likely to be constrained
by routine or inertia.

32:24.280 --> 32:25.510
Do you know what "negative space"
in architecture

32:25.510 --> 32:27.240
is usually meant to emphasize?

32:28.160 --> 32:30.640
It's openness

32:31.010 --> 32:31.860
and flow.

32:34.160 --> 32:35.440
And openness and flow

32:36.040 --> 32:37.900
bring limitless possibilities.

32:39.750 --> 32:41.480
Alright, stop checking it.

32:41.480 --> 32:42.720
You're not dreaming.

32:44.700 --> 32:46.700
How will you get back? It's raining.

32:47.400 --> 32:48.400
I brought an umbrella,

32:48.400 --> 32:49.750
and the coffee shop is just nearby.

32:49.750 --> 32:51.080
-I can walk back.
-Okay.

32:51.310 --> 32:51.810
What about you?

32:51.810 --> 32:53.510
How will you get a taxi in this rain?

32:53.510 --> 32:54.200
Me?

32:54.440 --> 32:56.300
My husband is coming to pick me up.

32:58.700 --> 33:00.000
I'll wait with you for a bit.

33:00.000 --> 33:01.000
No need.

33:01.000 --> 33:02.760
Aren't you starting work next Monday?

33:02.760 --> 33:04.290
Go home early and get ready.

33:04.370 --> 33:05.770
Don't show any weakness.

33:06.240 --> 33:06.960
Go now.

33:07.310 --> 33:08.040
I'm off then.

33:08.960 --> 33:09.640
Go on.

33:09.820 --> 33:10.420
Bye-bye.

33:20.670 --> 33:22.530
Why isn't he picking up his phone?

33:27.180 --> 33:28.780
I wonder what he's busy with.

34:00.830 --> 34:02.830
Hello, I'm here to report for work today.

34:02.830 --> 34:03.550
I'm Hu Xiu.

34:03.830 --> 34:04.720
Hu Xiu, right?

34:04.880 --> 34:05.610
Come with me.

34:14.800 --> 34:15.400
What's wrong?

34:15.400 --> 34:18.440
I-Is there something wrong
with my makeup?

34:18.920 --> 34:19.540
No.

34:19.570 --> 34:21.219
I'm just happy for you.

34:22.670 --> 34:24.280
When I saw your resume,

34:24.280 --> 34:26.610
I felt our work experiences were similar.

34:26.670 --> 34:28.630
I was also halfway down
a promising career path

34:28.630 --> 34:30.690
when I took a detour here to Shanghai.

34:32.100 --> 34:33.949
So do you regret it now?

34:35.270 --> 34:36.270
What do you think?

34:37.400 --> 34:39.130
Let's go. I'll show you around.

34:42.449 --> 34:44.250
This is Ms. Zhou's office,

34:44.360 --> 34:46.320
and Mr. Xiao's office is
on the second floor to the left.

34:46.320 --> 34:47.889
This is the conference room.

34:47.889 --> 34:50.550
Remember to book in advance
if you need to use it.

34:51.480 --> 34:52.870
This is the materials section.

34:52.870 --> 34:54.400
And this is the modeling area.

34:54.400 --> 34:55.780
The main office area is up ahead.

34:55.780 --> 34:58.180
Come on, I'll show you
to your workstation.

35:00.360 --> 35:01.420
Everyone, may I
have your attention please?

35:01.420 --> 35:03.560
I'd like to introduce our new colleague.

35:03.560 --> 35:04.560
This is Hu Xiu,

35:04.590 --> 35:06.280
our new assistant designer.

35:06.280 --> 35:08.610
She'll be working with us starting today.

35:09.230 --> 35:10.760
Hello everyone, I'm Hu Xiu.

35:10.760 --> 35:12.740
I'm very happy to be working
with all of you.

35:12.740 --> 35:15.010
I look forward to your guidance
and support.

35:15.010 --> 35:16.260
Welcome, welcome.

35:18.870 --> 35:20.330
This is your workstation.

35:20.380 --> 35:21.630
Let me introduce you to everyone.

35:21.630 --> 35:22.760
This is Jiang Tianyi,

35:22.760 --> 35:24.230
our lead architectural designer.

35:24.230 --> 35:25.360
This is Sun Yifei,

35:25.360 --> 35:26.230
senior architect.

35:26.230 --> 35:28.030
If you have any questions,
you can ask them.

35:28.030 --> 35:29.690
Of course, you can also ask me.

35:30.570 --> 35:32.920
Here are some forms you need to fill out
for your onboarding.

35:32.920 --> 35:33.740
Give them back to me once you're done.

35:33.740 --> 35:35.340
Got it. Thanks for your help.

35:39.150 --> 35:39.760
Mr. Jiang.

35:39.920 --> 35:40.510
Nice to meet you.

35:40.510 --> 35:41.440
Nice to meet you.

35:41.510 --> 35:43.150
You just graduated
from graduate school, right?

35:43.150 --> 35:45.970
Which overseas university did you attend
for your master's degree?

35:45.970 --> 35:46.530
I...

35:46.560 --> 35:48.080
I only have a bachelor's degree
from a domestic university.

35:48.080 --> 35:49.810
I graduated several years ago.

35:54.920 --> 35:56.070
Bachelor's degree is good.

35:56.070 --> 35:57.000
In our architecture industry,

35:57.000 --> 35:59.070
what matters is
accumulating work experience.

35:59.070 --> 36:00.000
While others were studying
for their master's,

36:00.000 --> 36:01.210
you were already
getting practical experience.

36:01.210 --> 36:03.110
That's much better than
theoretical knowledge.

36:03.110 --> 36:04.230
After graduation,

36:04.230 --> 36:06.960
I worked as a GM assistant
at a real estate company.

36:06.960 --> 36:09.330
I only recently decided to
return to architectural design.

36:09.330 --> 36:11.040
So strictly speaking,

36:11.370 --> 36:13.630
I don't have much practical experience.

36:24.590 --> 36:25.920
Hu... Xiu?

36:27.890 --> 36:28.480
Hu Xiu?

36:30.440 --> 36:31.440
Don't be nervous.

36:31.440 --> 36:32.750
Our company doesn't have that

36:32.750 --> 36:33.590
"everyone stand up when the boss arrives"

36:33.590 --> 36:35.150
kind of rule.

36:35.530 --> 36:36.220
Relax.

36:36.780 --> 36:37.510
Take it easy.

36:38.710 --> 36:39.630
Actually,

36:39.960 --> 36:41.400
Mr. Xiao and I

36:41.400 --> 36:42.850
had some minor conflicts before.

36:42.850 --> 36:45.250
I'm wondering
if I should apologize to him.

36:47.490 --> 36:49.260
Didn't you just start today?

36:50.710 --> 36:53.570
So did you somehow upset him
during your interview?

36:54.030 --> 36:56.320
Something like that.

37:00.440 --> 37:01.410
I think

37:01.880 --> 37:03.610
you should go apologize to him.

37:03.920 --> 37:05.150
Because

37:05.360 --> 37:06.030
the assistant designer position

37:06.030 --> 37:07.610
was created specifically for Mr. Xiao
this time.

37:07.610 --> 37:08.780
Your first project

37:08.810 --> 37:11.610
will definitely be
under Mr. Xiao's supervision.

37:11.760 --> 37:13.320
If there are issues

37:13.320 --> 37:14.790
that aren't clearly addressed,

37:14.790 --> 37:16.190
leaving things awkward,

37:16.600 --> 37:18.860
h-how can you work well together, right?

37:23.320 --> 37:24.070
Hu Xiu.

37:26.280 --> 37:27.010
Come up here.

37:46.230 --> 37:46.880
Mr. Xiao.

37:47.400 --> 37:48.530
You wanted to see me?

37:49.030 --> 37:50.290
Come in and have a seat.

37:58.560 --> 38:00.240
This is the project
we're currently working on.

38:00.240 --> 38:01.920
Take these materials
and review them carefully.

38:01.920 --> 38:02.720
Within a week,

38:02.950 --> 38:04.310
compile your thoughts and give them to me.

38:03.410 --> 38:04.090
[Lyman Group]

38:05.030 --> 38:06.220
Keep these materials confidential.

38:06.220 --> 38:06.950
Understood.

38:13.020 --> 38:14.220
Any other questions?

38:16.360 --> 38:17.030
Mr. Xiao.

38:19.000 --> 38:20.010
Hu Xiu, you're here too.

38:20.010 --> 38:20.700
Ms. Zhou.

38:21.320 --> 38:22.250
Perfect timing.

38:22.320 --> 38:23.540
Do you have any plans

38:23.570 --> 38:24.740
after work today?

38:25.510 --> 38:27.510
No. Is there some work to do?

38:28.090 --> 38:29.690
Not work. It's a dinner gathering.

38:29.690 --> 38:31.590
According to Dynamism's tradition,

38:31.590 --> 38:32.880
whenever a new employee joins,

38:32.880 --> 38:34.340
we treat everyone to dinner.

38:34.340 --> 38:35.270
Right, Mr. Xiao?

38:35.520 --> 38:36.720
You choose the place.

38:37.030 --> 38:38.110
Thank you, Boss.

38:40.070 --> 38:41.270
Are you done talking?

38:41.750 --> 38:43.710
Yes, I'll head down first.

39:06.330 --> 39:08.260
What on earth could he be busy with?

39:10.360 --> 39:11.110
Here we are.

39:11.110 --> 39:13.640
Thank you all for your hard work
this year.

39:13.660 --> 39:15.290
I hope that each of us

39:15.320 --> 39:16.670
can successfully complete

39:16.670 --> 39:18.230
our ongoing projects

39:18.230 --> 39:19.510
and achieve good results

39:19.510 --> 39:21.190
with the projects we're pursuing.

39:21.190 --> 39:22.030
Hear, hear!

39:22.490 --> 39:24.080
And now, for today's highlight:

39:24.080 --> 39:26.520
let's welcome our new colleague, Hu Xiu.

39:26.670 --> 39:28.230
I hope everyone can
get along well with her

39:28.230 --> 39:29.480
and make progress together.

39:29.480 --> 39:30.110
Welcome.

39:30.440 --> 39:31.000
Welcome.

39:32.430 --> 39:33.840
Here, a toast to you all.

39:34.360 --> 39:34.880
Come on.

39:35.000 --> 39:36.000
Cheers!

39:36.000 --> 39:37.480
Cheers!

39:37.480 --> 39:39.480
Newbie, aren't you joining us for a drink?

39:39.480 --> 39:41.200
We're all drinking alcohol.

39:41.440 --> 39:42.800
Yeah, have a drink.

39:43.070 --> 39:43.960
Today is the welcome party.

39:43.960 --> 39:44.960
You should at least have a drink too.

39:44.960 --> 39:46.150
Mr. Xiao. Ms. Zhou.

39:46.280 --> 39:47.740
I'd like to toast you both,

39:48.150 --> 39:49.210
and everyone else.

39:49.550 --> 39:50.760
Okay. Come on.

39:50.780 --> 39:51.490
Cheers.

40:02.320 --> 40:02.960
It's okay.

40:03.150 --> 40:04.610
I'll drive her home later.

40:05.050 --> 40:06.720
By the way, has she filled out
her onboarding form?

40:06.720 --> 40:07.480
Yes, she has.

40:07.660 --> 40:09.060
Is her home address on it?

40:09.440 --> 40:11.880
No. 27, Lane 9, Yanhua Road.

40:14.280 --> 40:16.470
No. 27, Lane 9.

40:18.770 --> 40:20.440
Isn't this Mr. Xiao's coat?

40:20.590 --> 40:22.260
Aren't these Mr. Xiao's shoes?

40:22.260 --> 40:22.720
This...

40:22.860 --> 40:24.530
This is Mr. Xiao's model.

40:24.710 --> 40:26.040
So Hu Xiu and Mr. Xiao...

40:26.420 --> 40:27.610
Live together?

40:31.550 --> 40:32.920
I'll give her a ride.

40:35.330 --> 40:36.390
It's on my way home.

40:36.860 --> 40:38.490
It does seem to be on the way.

40:39.030 --> 40:40.360
Fortunately, she looks like

40:40.360 --> 40:42.320
the type who just falls asleep

40:42.350 --> 40:44.480
when drunk, not the troublesome kind.

40:45.870 --> 40:46.520
Where do you live?

40:46.520 --> 40:47.650
I'll drive you home.

40:47.750 --> 40:48.460
I live...

40:49.190 --> 40:49.960
I live...

40:50.150 --> 40:52.190
I live on Yanhua Road.

40:53.560 --> 40:54.150
What?

40:55.360 --> 41:00.030
No. 27, Lane 9, Yanhua Road.

41:02.030 --> 41:02.560
Let's go.

41:16.790 --> 41:18.270
Don't touch me.

41:19.470 --> 41:21.760
Don't pull me! I said don't!

41:22.280 --> 41:23.340
Don't move around!

41:26.860 --> 41:27.340
I...

41:31.920 --> 41:33.380
Who took my command token?

41:34.230 --> 41:35.190
Who took my...

41:38.230 --> 41:40.230
Who's so wicked?

41:41.370 --> 41:43.370
I just want a command token.

41:43.400 --> 41:44.130
Here you are.

41:45.080 --> 41:46.560
I am the mayor!

41:48.510 --> 41:49.280
Yes, you are.

41:49.280 --> 41:49.800
You are.

41:50.420 --> 41:51.860
My command token.

41:52.250 --> 41:53.730
My token.

42:03.630 --> 42:04.190
Alright.

42:04.650 --> 42:05.780
We're here. Get off.

42:12.880 --> 42:13.510
Hu Xiu.

42:14.680 --> 42:15.320
Hu Xiu?

42:24.190 --> 42:25.960
Your mayor's command token is gone.

42:25.960 --> 42:26.760
What?
